  "prompt": "What are the best cooling pads for a MacBook Pro?",
  "response": "When looking for cooling pads for your MacBook Pro, it's important to consider factors such as cooling efficiency, build quality, ergonomics, and design. Here are some highly recommended cooling pads:\n\n1. **Thermaltake Massive TM**: \n   - Features adjustable temperature monitoring and control.\n   - Dual 120mm fans provide excellent cooling.\n   - Ergonomic design for comfortable typing.\n\n2. **Cooler Master Notepal X3**:\n   - Large 200mm fan for effective cooling.\n   - Ergonomic design for better comfort.\n   - Stylish LED lighting.\n\n3. **Kootek Cooler Pad Chill Mat 5**:\n   - Equipped with five fans for optimal cooling.\n   - Adjustable fan speed.\n   - Two-level height adjustment for better ergonomics.\n\n4. **HAVIT HV-F2056**:\n   - Slim, portable, and lightweight design.\n   - Three large 110mm fans for powerful cooling.\n   - Two adjustable height settings.\n\n5. **TopMate C5**:\n   - Comes with five fans (one large and four small) for extensive cooling.\n   - Adjustable height settings and fan speeds.\n   - Built-in display for controlling fan speed.\n\n6. **Targus Chill Mat**:\n   - Dual fans for good cooling performance.\n   - Comfortable ergonomic tilt.\n   - Integrated USB hub for additional connectivity.\n\n7. **TECKNET Laptop Cooling Pad**:\n   - Features two 110mm fans for efficient heat dissipation.\n   - Adjustable height settings.\n   - Lightweight and portable design.\n\n8. **Aicheson Laptop Cooling Pad**:\n   - Equipped with five fans for comprehensive cooling.\n   - Ergonomic design with adjustable height settings.\n   - Attractive LED lighting.\n\nWhen selecting a cooling pad, ensure it fits well with the size of your MacBook Pro and suits your use case, whether it's for gaming, heavy workflows, or everyday usage.",
